# Claude Code Rules for TariMarket L2

## Communication Style
- DO NOT use emojis in responses or documentation
- Be direct and technical
- Focus on facts and implementation details
- Avoid unnecessary enthusiasm or celebratory language

## Code Style
- Follow Rust conventions
- Use clear, descriptive variable names
- Add comments only when logic is non-obvious
- Prefer explicit error handling over unwrap()

## Documentation
- Write clear, technical documentation
- No marketing language or hype
- Focus on "what" and "how", not "exciting features"
- Use plain language without decorative symbols

## Responses
- Answer questions directly
- Don't add preamble or postamble
- Provide only requested information
- Be concise but complete
